  "body": "i use `$getConfig()` to fetch screen height,and then assign to `image` height.but it does not work,screen height is large than expects.\n\n```\n<template>\n  <scroller>\n    <image class=\"my_image\" style=\"width:750;height:{{height}}\" src = \"http://img.alicdn.com/bao/uploaded/i2/2547343901/TB2bPxhjFXXXXcnXpXXXXXXXXXX_!!2547343901-0-paimai.jpg_400x400.jpg\">\n    </image>\n  </scroller>\n</template>\n\n<style>\n\n</style>\n\n<script>\n  var modal = require('@weex-module/modal');\n  module.exports = {\n    data:{\n        height:''\n    },\n    methods : {\n      ready: function(){\n        var config = this.$getConfig();\n        var screenHeight = config.env.deviceHeight;\n        modal.toast({'message':'height:'+screenHeight,'duration':1});\n        this.height = screenHeight;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n</script>\n```\n"
